<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-02-03T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-02-03T12:00:00-05:00" n="506" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d506">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">882.01 Foreign Control/207:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Consul at Geneva (<persName corresp="#p_VSRG1" type="to">Gilbert</persName>)</hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-03T12:00:00-05:00">February 3,
                                        1932—noon</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>36. For <persName corresp="#p_RSJ1">Reber</persName>. Penultimate
                                paragraph your telegram 66, February 1, 6 p.m. There is no objection
                                to permitting in your discretion that publicity be given to your
                                memorandum, provided the same procedure is followed with respect to
                                any others on this subject which may have been submitted by other
                                members. Under Geneva date line the <hi rend="italic">New York
                                    Times</hi> yesterday reported your submission of the memorandum
                                together with an apparently accurate summary. Please send full text
                                by mail.</p>
                            <p>When do you anticipate the <hi rend="italic">rapporteur</hi> will
                                report to the Council?</p>
                            <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_SHL1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>